1
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:43,520
Wow, you're still here.

2
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:44,520
That is some perseverance.

3
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:46,520
I'm proud of you.

4
00:00:46,520 --> 00:00:47,520
Let's keep going.

5
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:51,800
I'm happy to report this is an easy one.

6
00:00:51,800 --> 00:00:55,000
Identity as a service.

7
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,000
What does that mean?

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:59,440
It means we can do any of the stuff that we have already talked about around identity

9
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:03,120
and access management, except that we can do it in the cloud.

10
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:04,120
That's identity as a service.

11
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:07,720
There's a little more to it than they need to know.

12
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:09,000
Here's the table.

13
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:12,760
There are a number of different identities that we can use in identity as a service.

14
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:15,760
So let's go through each of these and I'll provide you a nice simple definition of each

15
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:18,920
one.

16
00:01:18,920 --> 00:01:21,280
Let's start with cloud identity.

17
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:26,760
The idea of a cloud identity is that the identity, your information, your credential

18
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:32,320
information is entirely stored in the cloud and you authenticate in the cloud because

19
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:33,440
everything is stored in the cloud.

20
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:35,880
That's cloud identity.

21
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:41,320
Sync identity is where you have an identity in your local corporate store on premise and

22
00:01:41,320 --> 00:01:46,200
you have an identity in the cloud and sync means that they are connected and a change to

23
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:50,720
one is synchronized to the other, a change to this one is synchronized to the other one.

24
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:53,680
So sync identities, they're synchronized.

25
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:59,120
And the authentication can occur either on premise or in the cloud.

26
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:03,000
Federated identity is where you use federated access.

27
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:07,520
This whole process that we've already talked through about having three entities, the identity

28
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:12,240
provider, the relying party, the service provider, and the user or the principal.

29
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:16,120
And where the actual identity provider is located whether it's on premise or in the cloud

30
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,880
doesn't matter.

31
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:22,160
Federated identity is just this concept of using federated access.

32
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:25,680
And the last one is known as a linked identity.

33
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:30,160
This is where you still have two separate identities, one on premise and one in the cloud.

34
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:34,240
But the key difference between linked identity and synced identity, in sync, there was if

35
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:36,800
a change was made to one, it was synchronized to the other.

36
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:40,740
In linked, there's a connection to say that these are both accounts that belong to the

37
00:02:40,740 --> 00:02:46,680
same user, but an update to one does not synchronize automatically, update the other.

38
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:50,120
And so in linked identity, if you change this account in the cloud, it doesn't automatically

39
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:54,160
update this local account and vice versa.

40
00:02:54,160 --> 00:03:00,000
So those are the major types of accounts that we can use in the cloud.

41
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,640
And the final piece slide here is just related to what are all the services that we can have

42
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,000
in identity as a service.

43
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,160
And like I said, it's anything that you can do on premise, you can do provisioning,

44
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:12,600
you can do access management, you can do single sign-on, you can do multi-factor, all

45
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,560
of this stuff, you can do it in the cloud.

